Our Product

Monochrome living units are designed for immediate use, offering a fully plug-and-play solution suitable for a wide range of climates. These cabins are ideal as permanent dwellings or as hotel suites, with superior insulation and ventilation systems that guarantee both comfort and energy efficiency.



The cabins are built using a high-performance C24 certified timber frame, combined with 200mm of eco-friendly wool insulation. The external walls are protected by fiber cement Cembrit Patina® and thermowood cladding, which provide durability while maintaining a modern aesthetic. Inside, the cabin is fitted with MDF panels featuring natural oak finishes, adding both warmth and style to the living spaces.

The roof is designed for energy efficiency, using a waterproof EPDM membrane, 250mm of Ecowool insulation, and an integrated gutter system. This setup results in outstanding thermal performance, achieving U-values as low as 0.16 W/m²K for the roof, 0.18 W/m²K for the walls, and 0.16 W/m²K for the floors, making the cabins highly energy-efficient.

The interior is equipped with oak plank flooring, underfloor electric heating, and Daikin 12000 BTU AC for optimal climate control. A custom kitchen, complete with a quartz worktop, two-ring induction cooktop, and a small fridge, provides a high-quality and functional cooking area. The bathroom is designed with suspended Geberit® WC systems, stone resin vanity units, and sliding glass door showers, all complemented by ceramic stone tiles.

With advanced building materials and meticulous attention to energy efficiency, Monochrome living units combine modern design with top-tier technical performance, ensuring a comfortable and sustainable living environment.
